description:
maximum guaranteed HIGH off-state dc output current, of a 3-state digital function of an IC, at the maximum supply voltage and in a temperature range between specified temperatures (T_1 and T_2).
Applies to digital ICs with 3-state outputs. |It is assumed that the required external HIGH-state output voltage (V_OH or V_CC or V_DD) is applied, as well as the appropriate input condition (V_IL and/or V_IH).
